    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em>A barbazu beard is an intimidating helm with a full facemask wrought to look like a snarling barbazu&rsquo;s head. Extending from the chin area of the face guard is a razor-sharp blade much like an actual barbazu&rsquo;s beard, usually 8 inches long but sometimes longer.</em></p>\n<p>A barbazu beard can be used as an off-hand weapon that requires no hands to use; thus, a warrior could combine use of a barbazu beard with a two-handed weapon.</p>\n<p>Attacking with a barbazu beard provokes an attack of opportunity. Because it is so close to the wearer&rsquo;s face, using a barbazu beard against creatures harmful to touch (such as fire elementals and acidic oozes) has the same risks as using a natural weapon or unarmed strike against these creatures.</p>",
